				\begin{document}$$d_{1} \gg d_{2} , d_{3}$$\end{document} is best satisfied. 1D-like regions exhibit a different 1D morphology where the particles are short and matchstick-like. In some cases, the short 1D particles agglomerate into a larger mass where the morphology is not easily identified. These data were not included into the surrogate model, and yet they correlate well with the mixed morphology 1–2D and 2–3D regions of the landscape. The same is true of the dual morphology data points, which correctly occur in the mixed 1D–2D section of the landscape.
